## TEM Panel Reference — Identity, Security, and Admin Panels

### AdminUserPanel

| Field | Guidance |
|-------|---------|
| `User` | Teamcenter creates `infodba` as the admin user |
| `Password` | Set a compliant password during install — must not be empty, must not contain whitespace |

### OperationUserPanel

Initial installs typically use `infodba`. TEM may show values read-only in some flows.

### OSUserPanel

| Field | Guidance |
|-------|---------|
| `User` | Windows service account that will run Teamcenter services |
| `Password` | The service account password |

Requirements for the OS user:
- Must have local administrator rights
- Must have `Log on as a service` right
- Must be able to access the Teamcenter installation directory and `TC_DATA`

### SecurityPanel

Keep the security directory and password file storage secured under the Teamcenter data structure or a protected location.

### Password Rules Enforced by TEM

Applies to all password fields:

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| No empty passwords | TEM will not proceed with blank password fields |
| No whitespace | Passwords containing spaces will be rejected |
| Special characters | Some characters are rejected by TEM's system-user entry field — test with simple alphanumeric first if having issues |

### ProductExcellencePanel

Participation in Siemens product excellence program is enabled by default. Make an intentional choice and document it:

- Enabled: Telemetry data sent to Siemens
- Disabled: No telemetry sent
